ELYRIA, Ohio (AP) _ Invacare Corp. (IVC) on Tuesday reported fourth-quarter net income of $1.9 million, after reporting a loss in the same period a year earlier.On a per-share basis, the Elyria, Ohio-based company said it had profit of 5 cents. Earnings, adjusted for amortization costs, were 8 cents per share.The wheelchair, crutches and motorized scooter company posted revenue of $226.2 million in the period.For the year, the company reported that its loss widened to $45.6 million, or $1.31 per share. Revenue was reported as $872.5 million._____This story was generated by Automated Insights (http://automatedinsights.com/ap) using data from Zacks Investment Research. Access a Zacks stock report on IVC at https://www.zacks.com/ap/IVC